# Files excluded from the Vercel deployment upload.
#
# WHY: without this file the CLI uploaded the whole working directory — 293 MB,
# almost all of it reels/_frames (2.8 GB of rendered video frames on disk).
# Vercel answered the oversized upload with an HTML error page, which the CLI
# tried to parse as JSON and reported as:
#   Error: Unexpected token '<', "<html><h"... is not valid JSON
#
# Only exclude things the BUILD does not need. The build runs on Vercel, so
# app/, components/, lib/, content/ (MDX), public/ and the config files must all
# stay. Nothing below is imported by the application.

# Local video/reel generation workspace — nothing imports it
reels/

# Brand source assets (working files; shipped assets live in public/)
brand/
design/

# One-off and maintenance scripts, not part of the build
scripts/

# Docs and planning notes.
# Leading slash matters: a bare "*.md" would match at every depth, and the
# content loaders (lib/atlas.ts, lib/blog.ts, lib/academy.ts …) all accept .md
# as well as .mdx — so an unscoped rule would silently drop any .md entry from
# production the day one is added. Root-level only.
docs/
/*.md

# Database migrations are applied through Supabase, not at build time
supabase/

# Local build/tooling artefacts
.next/
node_modules/
.git/
*.tsbuildinfo
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
